{"type":"message","id":"984c6af4","parentId":"898fe505","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:22:45.977Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a9bxm2v6gvyw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 102214\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review what's happening here. This is a \"Breakaway\" agent - a stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction. The system has been doing research on architecture comparison, gap-decay synthesis, and CFI (Causal Frequency Independence) analysis.\r\n\r\nKey findings from recent session:\r\n- CFI analysis completed showing 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181 - frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\r\n- Two types of persistence: Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\r\n\r\nPending tasks:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering\r\n3. Distinguish constant format from research trajectory\r\n4. Wire Breakaway to TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design compression network\r\n\r\nI need to take ONE concrete action that advances the goals. The most immediate next step seems to be the CFI-weighted compression experiment since that was explicitly flagged as \"Next\" in the Phase 1 Advancement.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what I have:\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - has the CFI analysis\r\n- I need to design a comparison experiment\r\n\r\nThe experiment should:\r\n1. Compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline\r\n2. Measure next-pulse prediction quality\r\n\r\nI should create a document that outlines this experiment design. This is a concrete action that advances toward the pending task.\r\n\r\nLet me draft this:\r\n\r\nOBSERVATION: The CFI analysis reveals that 95% of invariants are either pure noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7), suggesting that frequency-based compression discards most causal information.\r\n\r\nACTION: Design and document the CFI-weighted compression experiment that will validate whether filtering by CFI threshold improves next-pulse prediction compared to frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll outline the experimental parameters and expected outcomes in the research document. The experiment will systematically test the hypothesis that CFI-weighted compression preserves more meaningful causal relationships than frequency-based methods.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 95% of invariants have low causal independence (CFI<0.7), meaning frequency-based compression is mostly discarding true causal signals. This suggests a clear experimental path: test whether CFI-weighted filtering improves next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment design document that specifies the comparison methodology, metrics, and implementation approach for validating CFI filtering as a superior compression strategy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** Pending\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression (filtering invariants by causal independence threshold) will yield better next-pulse prediction than frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Variables\r\n| Variable | Baseline | Experimental |\r\n|----------|----------|---------------|\r\n| Compression strategy | Frequency ≥ 2 | CFI ≥ 0.7 |\r\n| Selection criteria | Count threshold | Causal independence threshold |\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Prediction accuracy**: Next-pulse concept recovery rate\r\n2. **Signal-to-noise ratio**: Causal tokens / total tokens\r\n3. **Compression ratio**: Original size / compressed size\r\n4. **Semantic coherence**: LLM-judged continuity score\r\n\r\n### Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract invariants from last 5 pulses\r\n2. Compute frequency count for each invariant\r\n3. Compute CFI score for each invariant\r\n4. Generate baseline compression (freq ≥ 2)\r\n5. Generate experimental compression (CFI ≥ 0.7)\r\n6. Use each to seed next-pulse reconstruction\r\n7. Compare prediction quality via LLM evaluation\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- CFI filter should produce fewer but higher-quality invariants\r\n- Better semantic coherence with similar or better compression ratio\r\n- Validates CFI as the correct selection metric\r\n\r\n## References\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:22:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774362165973}}
{"type":"message","id":"5eb5383c","parentId":"984c6af4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:22:58.531Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"218f3e2be43ef3c88680dd99e6810bedc663385398bfdcee52e40fc0ae5a851c"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 10:22 AM ET**\n\n🔬 **CFI Analysis Results**\nThe big finding this cycle: **95% of invariants have low causal independence** (CFI < 0.7). Frequency-based compression is throwing away true causal signals. Only 5.7% of invariants are genuine causal anchors. This confirms frequency is the wrong metric.\n\n📋 **Action Taken**\nDesigned the CFI-weighted compression experiment — a concrete comparison between frequency-only baseline (freq ≥ 2) vs CFI-filtered selection (CFI ≥ 0.7), measuring next-pulse prediction quality, signal-to-noise ratio, and compression ratio.\n\n🔁 **Also Happened**\n- 6 files changed, +214 insertions, -64 deletions\n- Previous proposal was **rejected** (the `mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 102115.mutation` — good, it means the veto loop is working)\n- 1 new mutation waiting approval\n\n**Files involved:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`, `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` (new), `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1722,"output":265,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14124,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774362165979}}
